President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Doug Manchester as Ambassador to the Bahamas. If confirmed, Doug Manchester, also known as "Papa" Doug Manchester, will serve as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Commonwealth of the Bahamas. Manchester is a prominent industrialist with achievements in various fields such as telecommunications, radio broadcast, medical instrumentation, publishing, and real estate development. He has been the Chairman of Manchester Financial Group since 1970, which includes divisions like Manchester Grand Resorts and M Commercial Properties. Manchester is also involved in philanthropy through the Manchester Charitable Foundation and serves on the Board of Trustees of The Sanford Burnham Medical Research Institute. He holds a B.S. degree from San Diego State University.